  "raw_html": "<button type='button' role='link' class='btn btn-link p-0 text-start' id='link_5' aria-label=\" Virender Pal @ Vipin versus State of Haryana pdf\"  class='noToken' href='#' onclick=javascript:open_pdf('5','2025','2025_5_1054_1069','2025INSC710'); ><font size='4'> <strong>VIRENDER PAL @ VIPIN<span class='fst-italic'> versus </span>STATE OF HARYANA </strong>- <span class='escrText'>[2025] 5 S.C.R. 1054</span><span class='ncDisplay'>2025 INSC 710</span><input type='hidden' id='cnr' value=ESCR010005802025></button></font><br><strong>Coram : VIKRAM NATH<sup style=\"color: #268e97;font-size: 22px;top: 0;\" class=\"tooltip-sup\" data-tooltip=\"Author\">*</sup>, SANJAY KAROL, SANDEEP MEHTA</strong><br> Issue for Consideration Issue arose as regards correctness of High Court order dismissing the appeal of the accused-appellant and upholding his conviction u/s.304-B of Penal Code, 1860. Headnotes&dagger; Penal Code, 1860 &ndash; s.304-B &ndash; Dowry death &ndash; Persistent harassment and dowry to victim-deceased &ndash; Complainant-father of deceased gave dowry to appellant and his family but they remained dissatisfied and started subjecting deceased to harassment, taunts, and physical abuse &ndash; Panchayat meeting was called where appellant demanded certain sum from family of<br><strong class='caseDetailsTD' ><span style='color:#212F3D' > Decision Date :</span><font color='green'> 15-05-2025</font><span style='color:#212F3D' > | Case No :</span><font color='green'> CRIMINAL APPEAL No. 342/2015</font><span style='color:#212F3D' > | Disposal Nature :</span><font color='green'> Dismissed</font>   <span style='color:#212F3D' > |  Bench :</span><font color='green'> 3 Judges</font></strong><div class='row my-1 mt-2 border bg-light'><div class='col-auto'><a href='#' class='btn btn-outline-secondary btn-sm my-1' onclick=open_splitview('5','2025','2025_5_1054_1069','2025INSC710','S')><i <i class='fas fa-columns me-2'></i>Split view</a></div><div class='col-auto'><a